The article presents statements of support for the U.S.-Korea Trade Agreement from various politicians, organizations, and companies. Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell and Senator John Kerry both express their approval of the agreement, highlighting the potential for economic growth and job creation. Senator Maria Cantwell emphasizes the benefits the agreement would have for Washington state, particularly in terms of duty-free access to the Korean market for food products. Other statements of support come from organizations such as AT&T, PhRMA, American Meat Institute, and Walmart, all of which believe that the agreement will create new opportunities for their respective industries. The article also includes statements from the Entertainment Industry Coalition, which believes that the agreement will benefit the U.S. entertainment industry and support the growth of the creative economy.